items.name: Word-Find-Java-
items.description: I developed a Java program that allows users to input a letter grid and search for words within it. The program can handle grids of any size and searches in all directions—horizontally, vertically, and diagonally, both forwards and backwards. Users type in a word, and the program either finds it in the grid or indicates that it's not present.

items.description: This C# project uses Microsoft Office Interop Excel to read and analyze Excel files. Users can open a file, select criteria like units sold or revenue, and get reports on top-performing items, sales reps, and regions. The app provides dynamic summaries based on user input.
